"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-26-nigeria-vs-cameroon-super-falcons-starting-xi-for-paris-olympic-qualifier-out\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons head coach, Randy Waldrum has released the starting 11 to face Cameroon in the third round second leg 2024 Olympic Games qualifying fixture.  Waldrum released the list in a post via the Super Falcons' official X account.  The match will take place on Monday evening by 4pm.  The first leg encounter had ended in a 0-0 draw last Friday.  Here is Super Falcons' starting XI against Cameroon:  Chiamaka Nnadozie, Ashleigh Plumptre, Osinachi Ohale, Oluwatosin Demehin, Michelle Alozie, Deborah Abiodun, Christy Ucheibe, Jennifer Echegini, Toni Payne, Esther Okoronkwo and Rasheedat Ajibade.  The second leg match will take place at the MKO Abiola National Stadium, Abuja.  Waldrum makes two changes for Super Eagles vs Indomitable Lionesses  EPL: Arteta receives double injury boost ahead of Sheffield Utd vs Arsenal clash  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"